The luxury and fashion Hermes group is forecasting  moderate growth for this year, "probably at a more moderate rate than in  1993," according to the group's annual report out Tuesday.
In 1993, the group made a turnover of 2.85 billion francs (500 million  dollars), up 16 percent on 1992 and a net result of 210 million francs (36.8  million dollars), up 19 percent.
The group would be launching a new woman's perfume at the end of the year  to compensate for decline in sales, the report also said.
